This Mask Has A chokehold in ME 🤌🏻✨

I gave the @medicube_global_official Night Collagen Wrapping Mask a go, and wow — this one truly feels like a skin reset button. 💤✨

The texture surprised me at first — it’s thick, almost like a jelly balm, but it melts beautifully into the skin without feeling greasy or heavy. Once applied, it created this light, breathable film that locked in all the moisture from my nighttime routine.

The best part? Waking up to insanely plump, smooth skin. My face felt firm yet soft, like it drank a full glass of collagen overnight. No stickiness, no residue — just a healthy, nourished glow. 🌙💧

Perfect for nights when your skin feels tired, dry, or just needs a little extra love. It’s like a facial in your sleep. Definitely a game-changer in my PM skincare routine!

I used to dread sunscreen days — oily shine, clogged pores, white cast… you name it. 😩 

But then @beautyofjoseon_official Relief Sun SPF50+ walked into my skincare routine like a breath of fresh rice-infused air. 🌾💛

Lightweight like a moisturizer, glides on skin like silk, and leaves zero white cast. ZERO. ✨ 
As an oily-skin girl, that’s a big deal. 

No greasy finish, no stickiness — just a soft, healthy glow that stays fresh all day long.

Even under makeup, it doesn’t pill or feel heavy. And with ingredients like rice extract and probiotics, it’s giving hydration + protection in one smooth layer. 🙌

Honestly? It doesn’t even feel like sunscreen — and that’s exactly why I love it.

If you’ve been hunting for your oily-skin SPF soulmate, and want to skip moisturizer,this might just be it. 🤍

I definitely wouldn’t recommend to you all ❌
Else you all will fall in love with @laneige_in Hydra UV Sun defence Sunscreen 🤌🏻♥️

Thanks @maccaron_beauty for making me try this out and fall in love with it.
If you’re on the hunt for a sunscreen that delivers hydration without the greasy feel, the Laneige Hydra UV Defense Sunscreen might just be your next skincare favorite.

My Experience:
Texture: It has a lightweight, watery-gel consistency that glides on effortlessly. No white cast, no stickiness—just smooth, silky skin.

Hydration: True to its name, this sunscreen is ultra-hydrating. 

Finish: Leaves a dewy finish that gives the skin a healthy glow.

Performance: It offers great sun protection—I didn’t experience any tanning or irritation, even on days I was outdoors for long hours.

Cons:
Dewy finish may not suit oily skin types
Slight fragrance (if you’re sensitive to scents)

Laneige nailed it with this formula. I love how it makes my skin feel plump and protected without that heavy sunscreen feel.
